title: Top performers, Oct. 14, 2015
text:
Top performers, Oct. 14, 2015 Football Austin Archangel and Xavier Scott, Vilseck: The Falcon duo delivered a signature win for the program on Saturday, a 14-10 defeat of 2013 European champion and 2014 runner-up Wiesbaden. Archangel found Scott for a 33-yard touchdown pass midway through the fourth quarter that held up as the game-winning score. Fritz Sherenco, Alconbury: The Dragon quarterback led his team to its first win of the season on Saturday, a 42-6 rout of Baumholder. Sherenco collected 96 rushing yards, 87 passing yards and a touchdown of each variety. Volleyball Hannah Thomascall, Kaiserslautern: The Raiders picked up their first victory of the season Saturday, beating Division I rival SHAPE 25-21, 25-20, 19-25, 18-25, 22-20. The senior paced the marathon win with 10 aces, three kills and two blocks. Brigantia O’Sadnick, Wiesbaden: The unbeaten Warriors stayed that way Saturday while knocking Black Forest Academy from the ranks of the undefeated. O’Sadnick fueled the straight-set win with four aces, seven kills and six blocks. Jordan Wakefield, Vicenza: Wakefield stood out against a backdrop of Cougar stars with standout efforts in wins over American Overseas School of Rome and Aviano last weekend. She totaled 19 kills and 10 blocks across seven sets. Cross country Hunter Ficenec and Nina Gante, Stuttgart: The Panthers were absolutely dominant in a four-team home meet Saturday, finishing with the top three runners in both the boys and girls races. Ficenec and Gante picked up the respective top finishes. Tennis Austin Ward, Ramstein: The Royal ace paced a sweep of visiting Bitburg on Saturday. Ward won at No. 1 singles 6-0, 6-0 and at No.1 doubles 6-0, 6-1. Anouchka Laurent Josi, International School of Brussels: The Raider junior and rising championship contender has yet to drop a game this fall. Her latest 6-0, 6-0 romp came Saturday against Lakenheath. Join the conversation and share your voice.
